articles.description: It's been a historic season for the Xavier, but as the No. 4 Musketeers try to lock down their first Big East Conference title and a possible No. 1 seed in the NCAA Tournament, they'll have to find a way to topple No. 3 Villanova on Saturday afternoon...
articles.headline: No. 4 Xavier hosts No. 3 Villanova in marquee clash

articles.description: In its run to the national title game last season, Gonzaga found a strength not normally associated with Zags basketball: defense.
articles.headline: No. 9 Gonzaga hosts last-place Pepperdine

articles.description: Throughout the course of what has been a challenging and emotional season both on and off the court, Tom Izzo has gone back to coaching basics -- and it seems to be working.
articles.headline: No. 2 Michigan St. goes for 10th in row at Northwestern

articles.description: It's the time of year when every college basketball game sparks conversation about NCAA Tournament credentials -- whether a team is a lock, looks good or is surfing on the bubble.

articles.description: Rhode Island guard E.C. Matthews has been given the go-ahead to play against St. Bonaventure on Friday night, three days after the 16th-ranked Rams' second-leading scorer hurt his left knee.
articles.headline: Rhode Island guard E.C. Matthews given go-ahead to play after hurting left knee

articles.description: USC's Bennie Boatwright, who was averaging 13.6 points and 6.4 rebounds per game, is out for the season with a knee injury.
articles.headline: USC's Bennie Boatwright out for season with knee injury
